    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This unit utilizes a double-VANOS variable valve timing system and six individual throttle bodies to produce a linear power delivery and a distinctive metallic rasp. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M Differential Lock. The chassis integrity is excellent, with the critical rear subframe mounting points already inspected and reinforced. The suspension retains its factory-spec damping characteristics, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear configuration for precise turn-in. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain remains robust with documented rod bearing service and a cooling system refresh. An ideal specimen for the enthusiast seeking an analog driving experience with peak mechanical engagement.",
      "price": 34500.0,
